1
00:00:00,667 --> 00:00:02,500
<i> I'm here to talk to Luna.</i>

2
00:00:02,633 --> 00:00:03,533
<i> She's not here.</i>

3
00:00:03,667 --> 00:00:04,700
<i> Go away.</i>

4
00:00:05,467 --> 00:00:08,367
<i>It's good to hear that
you haven't forgotten me.</i>

5
00:00:08,833 --> 00:00:09,733
<i> What's going on?!</i>

6
00:00:10,633 --> 00:00:12,600
<i>Hello, boss.
We already have Juan.</i>

7
00:00:13,133 --> 00:00:14,833
<i> A map of Hotel 88?</i>

8
00:00:14,967 --> 00:00:16,800
<i> Why would Juan have this?</i>

9
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:17,933
<i> But what is this?</i>

10
00:00:18,067 --> 00:00:19,067
<i> Look.</i>

11
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:20,200
<i> What is that?</i>

12
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:22,933
<i>Do you think Andy is
telling the truth?</i>

13
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:24,200
<i> Nope.</i>

14
00:00:24,333 --> 00:00:26,233
<i>If you don't stop
what you're doing, Leon...</i>

15
00:00:27,567 --> 00:00:29,300
<i>you'll find yourself
in big trouble.</i>

16
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:31,067
<i>Leave me alone,
Martin Madrigal.</i>

17
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:32,233
<i> She hung up on me.</i>

18
00:00:32,367 --> 00:00:33,967
<i> You hurt her feelings, sir.</i>

19
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:35,533
<i> If I had let them do that,</i>

20
00:00:35,667 --> 00:00:37,233
<i>they would've taken
advantage of her!</i>

21
00:00:37,367 --> 00:00:40,033
<i>You are dead.
Looks like you've been marked.</i>

22
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:43,433
[CHANTING]

23
00:00:43,567 --> 00:00:44,800
- Grandpa?
- Hmm?

24
00:00:44,933 --> 00:00:47,633
Won't all the smoke stick
to Sir Martin?

25
00:00:47,767 --> 00:00:48,633
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

26
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:49,900
What do you mean?

27
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:51,567
I commence the ritual this way.

28
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:57,367
When someone enters
the house with negative energy.

29
00:01:01,233 --> 00:01:05,233
[CHANTING CONTINUES]

30
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:09,467
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

31
00:01:09,633 --> 00:01:11,267
[BOTONG HUMMING]

32
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:13,433
[BIRDS CHIRPING IN DISTANCE]

33
00:01:13,567 --> 00:01:14,700
Dark.

34
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:16,067
[FIRE CRACKLING]

35
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:19,567
I see... darkness.

36
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:21,267
Pitch-black!

37
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:24,267
That's going to come out
really dark, Grandpa.

38
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,800
The smoke is intense.

39
00:01:26,167 --> 00:01:27,433
My armpits reek?

40
00:01:27,933 --> 00:01:30,467
Oh no, Grandpa. I said smoke.

41
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:31,900
Do you want me to direct
smoke at you?

42
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:33,067
U-Uh...

43
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,167
My gosh, sir. He saw nothing
but darkness.

44
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:36,867
- [BOTONG] Mmm.
- That's what you said, right?

45
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,100
Toxic!

46
00:01:38,233 --> 00:01:40,000
- That's true.
- Your energy is toxic, sir.

47
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:41,100
There we go.

48
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:44,233
- Your energy is toxic.
- [MONETTE] I knew it.

49
00:01:44,367 --> 00:01:48,000
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

50
00:01:48,133 --> 00:01:51,000
Away, dark energy!

51
00:01:51,133 --> 00:01:52,533
Leave at once!

52
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:54,500
[SARI] That's right, Grandpa.

53
00:01:54,633 --> 00:01:58,300
Use the smoke on people
like Sir Martin.

54
00:01:58,433 --> 00:01:59,433
Get out!

55
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:08,333
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

56
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,867
Drink this.

57
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,767
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

58
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:09,767
Drink it, and the darkness
within shall be expelled.

59
00:03:10,533 --> 00:03:12,800
- Drink it.
- [MONETTE] Do as he says, sir.

60
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:14,800
[BOTONG] Drink.

61
00:03:16,933 --> 00:03:18,900
Release your hold on his...

62
00:03:19,667 --> 00:03:20,667
Gargle it.

63
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:22,633
I said gargle it.

64
00:03:22,767 --> 00:03:23,900
Gargle with force!

65
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:26,900
Oh, the darkness within...

66
00:03:27,033 --> 00:03:30,867
Keep on gargling and gargling.

67
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:34,567
Now spit out
the negative energy.

68
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:37,167
Spit it out.
Every single drop.

69
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:39,033
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

70
00:03:39,167 --> 00:03:40,300
Good.

71
00:03:43,267 --> 00:03:48,433
Dark energy lingers still.

72
00:03:50,867 --> 00:03:53,867
Depart, foul energy!

73
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,900
[DOOR OPENS]

74
00:03:56,033 --> 00:03:56,900
[SARI WHISPERS] Grandpa!

75
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:58,867
Close the door!

76
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:00,167
[DOOR CLOSES]

77
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:01,767
Is he still here?
Is he?

78
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:03,367
Yes, he's still here.

79
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:05,333
Why didn't you make him leave?!

80
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:09,033
I performed all sorts
of rituals, and yet...

81
00:04:09,167 --> 00:04:13,433
...he still went along
every single time.

82
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:16,067
He was raised with respect.

83
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:18,133
Seriously, Grandpa? Respect?

84
00:04:18,267 --> 00:04:20,333
He said all those words
to me, remember?

85
00:04:20,467 --> 00:04:24,233
The guy is just really bad
at communicating.

86
00:04:24,367 --> 00:04:26,067
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

87
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:30,800
On the day heaven weeps,

88
00:04:32,133 --> 00:04:34,900
its tears will fall
to the ground.

89
00:04:36,367 --> 00:04:38,567
Isn't that the sign you wanted?

90
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:39,467
[SARI SCOFFS]

91
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:40,667
[TENDER MUSIC PLAYING]

92
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:43,833
I think that's why
Martin came...

93
00:04:44,967 --> 00:04:50,300
So the day would not arrive
when heaven itself wept.

94
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,500
Grandpa?

95
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,633
[BOTONG] Maybe...

96
00:04:55,633 --> 00:04:57,800
he defended you from the guest

97
00:04:57,933 --> 00:05:00,567
who wanted to take
advantage of you...

98
00:05:01,233 --> 00:05:03,667
so you would not cry

99
00:05:05,167 --> 00:05:09,267
and let your tears
hit the ground.

100
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,733
[TENDER MUSIC CONTINUES]

101
00:05:11,867 --> 00:05:13,267
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

102
00:05:18,433 --> 00:05:24,300
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

103
00:05:24,433 --> 00:05:26,200
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

104
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:28,233
I'll just bring your shirt
to the laundromat.

105
00:05:29,033 --> 00:05:32,000
No. That's not what
I came here for, anyway.

106
00:05:32,133 --> 00:05:33,900
Sir, if it's about work,

107
00:05:34,067 --> 00:05:35,400
I left nothing pending.

108
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,900
Everything has been
turned over to Raphie.

109
00:05:38,033 --> 00:05:39,100
[MARTIN] You forgot something.

110
00:05:39,233 --> 00:05:40,333
[SARI]
Huh? That's not possible.

111
00:05:40,467 --> 00:05:42,033
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

112
00:05:42,167 --> 00:05:43,167
Actually...

113
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:44,533
A favor.

114
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:48,633
Come with me to another meeting
with Uncle Ronald.

115
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,500
Sir, just confess to him that
we're not really a couple.

116
00:05:57,633 --> 00:05:59,300
- Or I could tell him--
- No.

117
00:05:59,433 --> 00:06:00,967
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:02,067
I-I mean...

119
00:06:03,267 --> 00:06:04,933
It's not the right time yet.

120
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:07,633
His wife wants to meet you.

121
00:06:08,467 --> 00:06:09,533
And if I confess to him now,

122
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:11,900
he won't trust me
with the investment.

123
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:16,033
But, sir, I don't think
that it's right

124
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,967
for you to lie to him.

125
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:19,833
Look.

126
00:06:19,967 --> 00:06:22,367
Sari, I know I said
some words before.

127
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:24,667
But I only did so because...

128
00:06:25,633 --> 00:06:27,333
because I was protecting...

129
00:06:29,567 --> 00:06:32,167
Because I was protecting
the interests of the hotel.

130
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:34,267
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

131
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,500
Ah.

132
00:06:36,333 --> 00:06:37,400
The hotel.

133
00:06:38,033 --> 00:06:41,000
Sari, if I were the only one
to gain from this,

134
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:42,700
I wouldn't have asked you.

135
00:06:43,633 --> 00:06:46,200
There really is a lot
at stake here.

136
00:06:46,333 --> 00:06:48,300
A lot of people
would lose their jobs.

137
00:06:48,433 --> 00:06:50,400
Gio and Kiko are
counting on it,

138
00:06:50,533 --> 00:06:52,800
just like Isla Solara's
tourism industry.

139
00:06:54,067 --> 00:06:55,033
Sir.

140
00:06:55,900 --> 00:06:57,933
Are you trying to make me
feel guilty?

141
00:06:58,067 --> 00:07:01,633
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

142
00:07:01,767 --> 00:07:03,533
I'm asking for your help.

143
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:10,933
I'll think about it.

144
00:07:11,067 --> 00:07:12,400
You will?

145
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:14,700
[SIGHS]

146
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:15,867
Okay.

147
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,733
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

148
00:07:18,867 --> 00:07:19,933
I'll wait.

149
00:07:21,367 --> 00:07:24,900
[BIRDS CHIRPING IN DISTANCE]

150
00:07:32,267 --> 00:07:36,867
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

151
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,133
Sir, what did she say?

152
00:07:43,533 --> 00:07:45,167
She'll think about it.

153
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:46,633
What?

154
00:07:46,767 --> 00:07:49,700
Think about it?
So, she's still not sure?

155
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:52,633
That's what she told you
after you admitted your fault?

156
00:07:54,167 --> 00:08:00,767
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

157
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:02,133
Hang on, sir.

158
00:08:02,267 --> 00:08:03,633
You said sorry, right?

159
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:09,200
Oh, come on, sir!

160
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:10,633
Things were going well!

161
00:08:10,767 --> 00:08:13,467
You inhaled all that smoke,
you were polite...

162
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:16,200
But you couldn't even say
the magic word?

163
00:08:16,333 --> 00:08:17,700
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

164
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:19,300
I...

165
00:08:19,433 --> 00:08:20,933
I what?

166
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:23,533
Well, sorry, okay?

167
00:08:23,667 --> 00:08:25,433
You're sorry
for not apologizing?

168
00:08:26,033 --> 00:08:29,967
Sir, you should be saying
that to Sari.

169
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:33,367
My goodness, sir.

170
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:40,533
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:08:41,067 --> 00:08:42,167
You guys need water.

172
00:08:42,733 --> 00:08:45,933
Watering doesn't matter
that much to me.

173
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:49,067
But to you guys, it's important.

174
00:08:50,167 --> 00:08:51,500
That's just how it is.

175
00:08:51,633 --> 00:08:53,467
My feelings
are important, right?

176
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,200
So what if he could
tell me that,

177
00:08:56,367 --> 00:08:57,633
- that--
- [UMBRELLA OPENS]

178
00:08:57,767 --> 00:09:01,833
- [WATER POURING]
- [ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

179
00:09:01,967 --> 00:09:03,367
[MARTIN] I forgot something.

180
00:09:09,867 --> 00:09:10,833
What is it?

181
00:09:15,633 --> 00:09:16,900
I'm sorry.

182
00:09:17,033 --> 00:09:20,033
["SILONG KA MUNA" BY BRYAN CHONG
PLAYING]

183
00:09:20,167 --> 00:09:21,533
Sorry for...

184
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:24,100
the things I've said to you.

185
00:09:32,033 --> 00:09:33,933
Uh... [COUGHS]

186
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:37,333
[STUTTERING] Sari...
Hold onto this yourself.

187
00:09:37,467 --> 00:09:38,667
Huh?

188
00:09:41,233 --> 00:09:42,433
That's all.

189
00:09:49,767 --> 00:09:50,733
Sari...

190
00:09:53,233 --> 00:09:54,467
I hope...

191
00:09:55,067 --> 00:09:56,467
You hope what?

192
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:59,767
I hope you consider
going back to the hotel.

193
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:11,633
Oh!

194
00:10:12,133 --> 00:10:13,600
He apologized!

195
00:10:13,733 --> 00:10:15,567
Universe, he apologized!

196
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:20,733
[SQUEALING]

197
00:10:20,867 --> 00:10:22,600
Universe!

198
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:28,200
[SQUEALING, GIGGLING]

199
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,000
[MONETTE] Here you go!

200
00:10:30,133 --> 00:10:31,933
It's from Kiko.

201
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:34,500
He told me to give it to you.

202
00:10:34,667 --> 00:10:37,433
He said he wishes it could bring
a smile to your face.

203
00:10:39,033 --> 00:10:40,867
Uh, where is he?

204
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,567
Uh, he and Cesar just took care
of something about housekeeping.

205
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:46,267
- Wait, I'll send him a message.
- Oh, you don't have to!

206
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:48,267
Uh, it's good.
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

207
00:10:50,067 --> 00:10:51,100
Um...

208
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:55,233
It's just... I don't want
to see him as of the moment.

209
00:10:56,567 --> 00:10:59,167
Why not? Did something happen
with you and Kiko?

210
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:03,600
He keeps confusing me, Monette.

211
00:11:03,733 --> 00:11:04,800
You know how...

212
00:11:05,567 --> 00:11:07,833
At times, we're like friends,

213
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,767
then sometimes it's as if...

214
00:11:10,533 --> 00:11:11,700
as if...

215
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:14,467
it's as if we're, uh...

216
00:11:15,333 --> 00:11:16,700
- [CLICKS TONGUE]
- More than friends.

217
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,333
Well...

218
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:24,133
Raphie told me that Kiko's
actions towards me,

219
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:25,833
the way we're close
with each other,

220
00:11:25,967 --> 00:11:28,167
the way he cares for me,

221
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:31,967
he said those things aren't done
just for a friend.

222
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:33,133
That's not always the case.

223
00:11:33,267 --> 00:11:34,867
Raphie just keeps on yapping
about anything.

224
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,600
Just saying stuff!

225
00:11:36,733 --> 00:11:38,767
There are some friends
who are really like that.

226
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:40,700
Very caring.

227
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:42,567
Just my two cents.

228
00:11:42,733 --> 00:11:45,000
But I think it's unfair
that you're avoiding him.

229
00:11:46,767 --> 00:11:48,933
Wait, you're saying I'm unfair?

230
00:11:49,067 --> 00:11:50,700
What I'm saying is...

231
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:53,567
Is it a sin that he
only sees you as a friend?

232
00:11:54,567 --> 00:11:56,700
When he went out of his way
to give you flowers

233
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:59,300
because he's worried.

234
00:12:00,433 --> 00:12:02,300
Do you think that it's fair

235
00:12:02,433 --> 00:12:04,467
to run away from someone
who's sincere?

236
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,467
Who's worried for you?

237
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:11,167
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

238
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:12,400
[DOOR CLOSES]

239
00:12:12,533 --> 00:12:19,633
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

240
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,300
- Dad.
- Hey. How was it?

241
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:24,533
Still no news from the Almazans?

242
00:12:25,300 --> 00:12:27,533
Still nothing, Dad. [SIGHS]

243
00:12:27,667 --> 00:12:28,767
Hmph.

244
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:30,100
Why? Do you think there's
something wrong

245
00:12:30,233 --> 00:12:31,867
with the agreement?

246
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:33,467
I don't think so.

247
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:35,633
Though Luna messaged me saying

248
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:38,800
that Leon is already reviewing
the contract with their lawyers.

249
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:40,500
Okay.

250
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:44,500
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

251
00:12:44,633 --> 00:12:46,433
Would you like me to follow
up on it, Dad?

252
00:12:46,567 --> 00:12:49,233
I don't think so.
There's no reason to.

253
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:51,900
Maybe they consulted it
with the Fernandezes too.

254
00:12:52,033 --> 00:12:54,033
Let's just wait. It's not just
the Almazans

255
00:12:54,167 --> 00:12:55,633
who we're making a deal with.

256
00:12:55,767 --> 00:12:56,900
Right, right.

257
00:12:58,533 --> 00:13:00,300
Alright, Dad. Um...

258
00:13:00,433 --> 00:13:01,667
I'll go and rest, okay?

259
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:04,267
Alright. Go ahead.
You had a long day.

260
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:05,733
- Good night, Dad.
- Good night.

261
00:13:10,033 --> 00:13:16,867
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

262
00:13:18,133 --> 00:13:20,733
[LINE RINGING]

263
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:23,733
Hello?

264
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:26,833
Keep an eye on Leon.

265
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:29,600
Report to me his every move.

266
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:34,333
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES,
FADES]

267
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:38,433
Where were you last night?

268
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:40,467
Huh?

269
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:42,433
What do you mean?

270
00:13:42,567 --> 00:13:44,667
I checked your room.
You weren't there.

271
00:13:45,267 --> 00:13:46,867
Maybe you just didn't notice me.

272
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:48,667
[SCOFFS]

273
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:51,000
Were you out
fighting someone again, huh?

274
00:13:51,133 --> 00:13:52,200
[LAUGHS] Yeah.

275
00:13:53,167 --> 00:13:54,933
Yeah I fought with someone
and got imprisoned.

276
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:56,933
That's a good excuse.
Let's go with that.

277
00:13:57,067 --> 00:13:59,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

278
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,367
What are up to this time?

279
00:14:06,067 --> 00:14:08,667
Are you gonna give an answer
to my question to you before?

280
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:11,767
You still won't?

281
00:14:13,533 --> 00:14:15,367
Then I'm not answering
your question.

282
00:14:16,667 --> 00:14:18,100
Oh!

283
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:19,633
I actually already have
an answer.

284
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:21,933
I got into a fight.

285
00:14:22,067 --> 00:14:24,233
That's what you think
of me anyway, right?

286
00:14:24,367 --> 00:14:25,867
So I'm going with that excuse.

287
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:32,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

288
00:14:34,233 --> 00:14:36,700
[AMBIENT NATURE SOUND]

289
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:38,100
[MONETTE] Has the boat arrived?

290
00:14:38,233 --> 00:14:39,467
I'll just take care
of the stuff I bought.

291
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,500
[RAPHIE] Okay.

292
00:14:40,633 --> 00:14:41,933
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

293
00:14:42,067 --> 00:14:43,967
[RAPHIE] You look
extra handsome today, sir.

294
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:46,667
Are we waiting for
a special guest?

295
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:48,900
It's not a guest,
but someone special.

296
00:14:49,033 --> 00:14:51,333
Well, the question is,
will that 'someone' come?

297
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:56,567
[RAPHIE] Is she on the boat
that just arrived?

298
00:14:56,700 --> 00:14:58,933
Hmm, got you!
I'm updated on the latest news!

299
00:14:59,067 --> 00:15:01,467
You already know
that we're sisters.

300
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:02,800
[POPS LIPS]

301
00:15:03,567 --> 00:15:05,000
She did not answer the phone.

302
00:15:06,233 --> 00:15:07,867
Oh, really?

303
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,200
Maybe you didn't
convince her enough, sir.

304
00:15:10,333 --> 00:15:11,400
What do we do?

305
00:15:17,033 --> 00:15:18,567
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

306
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:25,700
["SILONG KA MUNA"
BY BRYAN CHONG]

307
00:15:40,667 --> 00:15:47,700
["SILONG KA MUNA" CONTINUES]

308
00:15:57,900 --> 00:16:00,633
I thought you'd take care
of the stuff you bought?

309
00:16:00,767 --> 00:16:02,400
I definitely can't miss this.

310
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:07,967
Do I look pretty, sir?

311
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:10,800
I just thrifted this.

312
00:16:11,467 --> 00:16:12,433
Are you back?

313
00:16:13,667 --> 00:16:15,933
I mean,
not just for the meeting, but...

314
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,733
are you going back
to work at the hotel?

315
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:22,200
Sir, comeback is real.

316
00:16:23,467 --> 00:16:24,967
And this pretty face,

317
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,200
it's here for the long run.

318
00:16:28,133 --> 00:16:29,167
Oh, wow.

319
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:31,433
Beauty so long-lasting
like car batteries!

320
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,800
Uh...

321
00:16:33,933 --> 00:16:36,733
I-I made a list of things
you need to do today.

322
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:39,267
All of it should be done.

323
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:42,367
And I need a report
from every department and...

324
00:16:42,533 --> 00:16:46,300
And 101 tasks that I need to do.

325
00:16:49,667 --> 00:16:50,767
And...

326
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:53,833
eat up before you start.

327
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,100
Monette.

328
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:02,567
Uh, come on.
I prepared your favorite

329
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:09,500
["SILONG KA MUNA" CONTINUES]

330
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:13,100
Sister!

331
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:15,767
That was amazing! [SHRIEKS]

332
00:17:15,933 --> 00:17:18,333
[MONETTE, RAPHIE, SARI GIGGLING]

333
00:17:22,933 --> 00:17:24,233
[MUSIC FADES]

334
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:28,700
[STRONG BREEZE]

335
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:30,667
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

336
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:31,867
Justin.

337
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,967
Are you really not going
to the hotel with us?

338
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:35,700
Nope. I'm not going there.

339
00:17:35,833 --> 00:17:37,867
- Why not?
- I'm suspended, remember?

340
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,367
And you guys don't really
need me there.

341
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,600
- Justin!
- It's okay.

342
00:17:40,733 --> 00:17:41,767
I'm busy with something anyway

343
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:43,833
so it's good timing
that I'm suspended.

344
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:46,800
Ma'am, you have a visitor.

345
00:17:46,933 --> 00:17:50,433
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

346
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:51,533
Hi, Luna.

347
00:18:06,667 --> 00:18:13,467
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

348
00:18:17,433 --> 00:18:18,033
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

349
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,300
You guys should go ahead.

350
00:18:19,433 --> 00:18:20,433
Who's this?

351
00:18:22,033 --> 00:18:23,367
[LUNA] Come on.

352
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:25,067
I'll just follow you guys
to the hotel.

353
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:26,800
Go.

354
00:18:26,933 --> 00:18:27,900
[JUSTIN SCOFFS]

355
00:18:28,033 --> 00:18:31,100
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

356
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:34,000
Go.

357
00:18:34,133 --> 00:18:38,133
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

358
00:18:41,267 --> 00:18:43,100
Long time no see, babe.

359
00:18:43,967 --> 00:18:50,800
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

360
00:18:50,933 --> 00:18:51,833
[MUSIC FADES]

361
00:18:51,967 --> 00:18:58,200
- [STRONG BREEZE]
- [WOOD SQUEAKING]

362
00:18:58,367 --> 00:19:01,533
[INDISTINCT CHATTER IN DISTANCE]

363
00:19:01,667 --> 00:19:02,567
Gio!

364
00:19:03,467 --> 00:19:04,433
Gio!

365
00:19:05,033 --> 00:19:07,300
Have you seen Kiko?

366
00:19:07,433 --> 00:19:08,967
Huh?

367
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:11,500
I didn't, but I'm pretty
sure he's just around.

368
00:19:11,633 --> 00:19:12,767
Oh, okay.

369
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:18,500
Oh, please tell Martin
Luna is going to be a bit late.

370
00:19:18,633 --> 00:19:20,167
She has a guest over.

371
00:19:20,933 --> 00:19:21,900
Visitor?

372
00:19:22,033 --> 00:19:23,233
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

373
00:19:23,367 --> 00:19:25,233
Who? Do you know this visitor?

374
00:19:25,367 --> 00:19:28,033
I'm not sure, but it's a guy.

375
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,933
Luna didn't introduce him to us.

376
00:19:32,167 --> 00:19:34,033
I'll get going, Gio
I'll just look for Kiko.

377
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:41,400
- Kiko!
- Oh, Jade.

378
00:19:41,533 --> 00:19:42,233
Let's go?

379
00:19:42,367 --> 00:19:44,833
- To where?
- Just come!

380
00:19:44,967 --> 00:19:45,900
Let's go.

381
00:19:46,033 --> 00:19:48,500
[JADE GIGGLING]

382
00:19:48,633 --> 00:19:53,333
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

383
00:19:53,467 --> 00:19:55,100
Come on! Hurry!

384
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:56,167
Where are we really going?

385
00:19:56,300 --> 00:19:57,967
Just come with me. Let's go.

386
00:19:58,933 --> 00:20:00,167
What's up?

387
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:01,000
Secret.

388
00:20:01,133 --> 00:20:02,267
We're here.

389
00:20:07,467 --> 00:20:08,367
Let's go.

390
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:13,567
- Wow.
- [BOTH CHUCKLE SOFTLY]

391
00:20:14,433 --> 00:20:16,300
Hold on.
What are we celebrating, Jade?

392
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:18,700
Rice cakes
are your favorite, right?

393
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:25,033
You want some?

394
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,167
Go eat some first.

395
00:20:29,533 --> 00:20:30,767
[KIKO CHUCKLES]

396
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:32,733
[SOFT MUSIC FADES]

397
00:20:32,867 --> 00:20:34,700
[EXHALES]
With a view like this...

398
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:37,300
I get now why you left me.

399
00:20:39,067 --> 00:20:40,667
What do you want?

400
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,733
- You.
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

401
00:20:42,867 --> 00:20:44,133
I missed you.

402
00:20:45,867 --> 00:20:47,000
We hadn't talked
for a long time.

403
00:20:47,133 --> 00:20:49,100
That means I don't want you
in my life anymore.

404
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:50,567
But I'm still here.

405
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:51,767
I still want you.

406
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:53,767
I'm here

407
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:55,767
to take you back.

408
00:20:56,667 --> 00:20:58,100
The question is,

409
00:20:58,233 --> 00:20:59,400
do I still want you?

410
00:20:59,533 --> 00:21:00,667
[SNICKERS]

411
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:02,133
I know you do.

412
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:05,567
Solenn,

413
00:21:06,567 --> 00:21:07,600
Luna,

414
00:21:09,233 --> 00:21:11,500
whatever name they call you,

415
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,433
I'm calling you mine.

416
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,533
I'm done with the life
I had with you before.

417
00:21:23,967 --> 00:21:25,500
I will never get back
with you again.

418
00:21:25,633 --> 00:21:26,600
[PETER SNICKERS]

419
00:21:28,067 --> 00:21:31,100
Don't get ahead of yourself.

420
00:21:33,267 --> 00:21:34,533
You know me well.

421
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,367
I get what I want.

422
00:21:39,867 --> 00:21:41,033
Are you done?

423
00:21:42,133 --> 00:21:44,400
If you're done talking,
you can now leave.

424
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:48,367
Joe, he's leaving.

425
00:21:50,633 --> 00:21:51,600
[JOE] Sir.

426
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:58,033
Bye, babe.

427
00:21:58,167 --> 00:21:59,100
I'll see you soon.

428
00:21:59,233 --> 00:22:06,300
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

429
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:16,067
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

430
00:22:24,567 --> 00:22:25,900
<i>Is he the reason
why you left me?</i>

431
00:22:26,033 --> 00:22:28,033
<i>Is that really what you do?
Or maybe you're a two-timer?</i>

432
00:22:28,167 --> 00:22:30,467
<i>We're just starting
to be friends again.</i>

433
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:32,367
<i>No one should ever leave
this friendship.</i>

434
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:35,333
<i> It's okay, I'll wait.</i>

435
00:22:35,467 --> 00:22:37,400
<i>When you first met Sari
at the cemetery,</i>

436
00:22:37,533 --> 00:22:39,800
were you like, "she's the one"?

437
00:22:39,933 --> 00:22:41,333
<i> C-Cemetery?</i>

438
00:22:43,433 --> 00:22:44,733
<i>What do you know
about the treasure?!</i>

439
00:22:44,867 --> 00:22:46,733
<i>I don't know
what you're talking about!</i>

440
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:50,167
<i>There's just one way
to find answer to that.</i>

441
00:22:50,333 --> 00:22:51,633
<i> Let's go there.</i>

442
00:22:51,767 --> 00:22:54,333
<i>It's the only place close
to where I saw Dad and Uncle.</i>
